commitResults.messageTitle: Added Greet, Echo and Exit commands
commitResults.messageBody:
- Changed the format of all messages sent to user
- Changed greeting message
- Added support for user input (Specifically only 3 commands)

commitResults.messageTitle: Changed ECHO to ADD, added LIST commands
commitResults.messageBody:
- ECHO command has been changed to an ADD command to add to a database of strings
- LIST command added to list all stored strings

commitResults.messageTitle: Added Todo, Deadline, Event, reverted ADD to ECHO
commitResults.messageBody: Reverted ADD to ECHO since we do not want to add generic tasks

commitResults.messageTitle: Updated input and expected output for automated text UI testing
Added exceptions to handle errors and invalid commands. Removed echo

commitResults.messageBody: Added autosave capability to a save file named "tasks.txt". The save file will be automatically loaded upon the start of program execution, and upon any update to the list of tasks, this will be automatically rewritten to the save file to update it.

commitResults.messageTitle: Added support for proper Date and Time representation and DATE command
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadlines and events now represent datetime as a LocalDate object. This allows future manipulations of tasks using dates as well.

DATE command has been added to allow the query of tasks that are due/occur on the specified date.
Add Ui, Storage, Parser, TaskList classes
Divide into more sub-packages: duke.io and duke.data

Add unit tests for Parser and TaskList
Add equals() override methods for TaskList, Tasks, and Command
Add JavaDocs for every class and public/protected method

Added parsing and handling of new FIND command.

This enables the user to get a list of all tasks whose descriptions contain a given keyword/phrase
Checked through each class for coding standard violations to identifiers, formatting, etc
Updated the name of the function call to test the filtering by date for a TaskList

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Gradle checkstyle support and refactored code according to feedback
commitResults.messageBody:
Add Gradle checkstyle
Fix checkstyle issues
Incorporate PR review feedback

Remove text-based UI
Add GUI using JavaFX
Forgot to do Level-10 on separate branch
Fix checkstyle and prepare for gradle build to jar

Add assertions to check assumptions in code.

Assertions are added in the Storage class in order to check that the data we load is in a correct/good format.

Assertions are also added in Duke to check for index out of bounds.

These are put at specific points so that if they are caught, we know that something has gone wrong with the parsing of data, either in loading from disk or there are logical errors in the data loaded.

Refactor methods that follow poor coding quality practices.

Examples of poor code quality include:
* Long methods that can be refactored into multiple smaller ones
* Methods that have deep nesting (High levels of indentation)
* Magic numbers
* No SLAP

In order to ensure greater code readability and understanding at a glance, long methods were broken down into multiple smaller ones.

This should also make it easier to read how the happy paths will execute.

Add a new Task named DoWithinPeriodTask

A DoWithinPeriodTask indicates a task that contains a period, or specifically a start and end date to indicate the time period during which a task can/should be completed.

A new subclass of Task has thus be added to implement this, as this is a perfectly valid Task.

This new class can be saved to disk, formatted and marked as completed as per any other Task.
Allows proper creation and release of working jar file
InvocationTargetException was being unhandled when the program encounters the done and delete command without any parameters passed to it (Despite expecting one)
Add description of available features as well as guide for each available command, description of each command, and examples of usage.
